nstrate that [{OI}]\$\_\{{\textbackslash}rm 63{\textbackslash}mu m\}\$ can be used as a replacement for [{CII}] in high-redshift galaxies where [{CII}] is unobserved and argue that more observation time should be used to target [{OI}] at \$z{\textgreater}6\$. (Abridged)},
