t. We also study the variations observed in the strength of the nebular Heii\${\textbackslash}lambda1640\$ emission between the \$L({\textbackslash}rm H{\textbackslash}alpha)/L({\textbackslash}rm {UV})\$ subsamples. We find that variations in the upper-mass limit of the {IMF} cannot fully account for all the observed difference in the {HeII} emission between the \$L({\textbackslash}rm H{\textbackslash}alpha)/L({\textbackslash}rm {UV})\$ subsamples, and that another source of He\${\textasciicircum}\{+\}\$ ionizing photons, such as X-ray binaries, may be needed to explain such a difference.},
