d high ionisation state in z{\textasciitilde}6 galaxies conspire to maximise the [{OIII}] output from galaxies, yielding an [{OIII}] luminosity density at z{\textasciitilde}6 that is significantly higher than at z{\textasciitilde}2, despite the order of magnitude decline in cosmic star formation. Thus, [{OIII}] emission-line surveys with {JWST} prove a highly efficient method to trace the galaxy density in the epoch of reionization.},
